        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:25PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mercer, or 34 miles east of Garrison, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mcclusky, Mercer, and Hoffer Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
